One is that broadcast fusion may call a function more times than necessary. I wonder if the right place is in performance tips, like [here](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/manual/performance-tips/#More-dots:-Fuse-vectorized-operations), as that page has many examples. Perhaps with a sentence added here?

A simpler example without slices might be something like this:
```
julia> let x = rand(100, 100)
           y = sum(abs2, x; dims=2)
           @btime $x ./ sqrt.($y)     # calls sqrt 100^2 times
           @btime $x ./ map(sqrt, $y) # 100 calls, but allocates length 100
       end;
  min 18.042 μs, mean 24.067 μs (2 allocations, 78.17 KiB)
  min 2.863 μs, mean 8.403 μs (3 allocations, 79.05 KiB)
